{"expireTime":9007200881132592000,"key":"transformer-remark-markdown-ast-28b38bb50a0f67ee052bfa83387bc0ac--","val":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Both the browser and Node.js use JavaScript as their programming language.","position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":75,"offset":75},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":2,"column":1,"offset":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":75,"offset":75},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Building apps that run in the browser is a completely different thing than building a Node.js application.","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":77},"end":{"line":4,"column":107,"offset":183},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1,"offset":77},"end":{"line":4,"column":107,"offset":183},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Despite the fact that it's always JavaScript, there are some key differences that make the experience radically different.","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":185},"end":{"line":6,"column":123,"offset":307},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":1,"offset":185},"end":{"line":6,"column":123,"offset":307},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"From the perspective of a frontend developer who extensively uses JavaScript, Node.js apps bring with them a huge advantage: the comfort of programming everything - the frontend and the backend - in a single language.","position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":309},"end":{"line":8,"column":218,"offset":526},"indent":[]}}],"position":{"start":{"line":8,"column":1,"offset":309},"end":{"line":8,"column":218,"offset":526},"indent":[]}},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"You have a huge opportunity because we know how hard it is to fully, deeply learn a programming language, and by using the same language to perform all your work